George Ford is an artist and a pragmatist rolled into one and the England fly-half is quickly discovering that the latter trait is a more consistently valuable asset in international rugby.

The 21-year-old Bath playmaker spends most weekends with his club demonstrating the range of his attacking game — as a creative rookie able to unravel defences at close quarters. He has shown that part of his repertoire during this RBS 6 Nations, but is also having to embrace the earthier demands of his role, involving substance over style.

England’s defeat by Ireland in Dublin gave Ford a first-hand view of Jonny Sexton, the home fly-half, following orders to the letter and quelling his own instincts in the process. The Lions No 10 led an aerial onslaught which the visitors failed to handle.

